ce:section.ce:para:
Sensors were deposited on gold-plated IDEs embedded on a PCB substrate. Firstly, copper wires were mounted on both ends of the sensor using a conductive silver paste by soldering method. The wires were then rinsed with acetone prior to preparing the sensor films. Preparation of sensor films was carried out by drop casting method. Precisely 5 mL of the sensing materials dispersed in methanol solvent to form solution concentration of 3 mg/mL were drop casted on the IDE-PCB substrates using a micro-syringe (Fig. 2
                        ). As-deposited sensor devices were then air-dried and preheated using LCR-6300 multimeter for conditioning under normal air environment. Prior to taking gas measurements, each sensor was placed inside a 5 L test chamber filled with air, connected to LCR-6300 multimeter for pre-heating and stabilization for 1 h in order to achieve good ohmic contacts with a stable resistance baseline as shown in Fig. 3
                        .
